# Index for embed.go

File: internal/shared/certs/embed.go
Package: certs
Purpose: Statically embeds system root certificate authority PEM blocks for server verification and mTLS device authorization.

Globals and Init:
serverCACertPEM, deviceCACertPEM: raw bytes compiled from assets/server-ca.crt and assets/device-ca.crt via go:embed.

Functions:
func ServerCAPEM() []byte. Purpose: returns embedded server-ca.crt bytes for client-side transport security verification.
func DeviceCAPEM() []byte. Purpose: returns embedded device-ca.crt bytes for server-side device certificate validation.

Build: requires go 1.16+ due to go:embed directives.
Security Constraints: CA anchors are static and hardcoded into binaries. Rotation requires compilation.


# Index for loader.go

File: internal/shared/certs/loader.go
Package: certs
Purpose: Parses embedded CA PEM certificate arrays and constructs x509.CertPool trusted anchors for TLS/mTLS validation.

Constants and Vars:
ErrEmptyCA, ErrInvalidCACert: domain-specific x509 parsing validation errors.

Functions:
func LoadServerCAPool() (*x509.CertPool, error). Purpose: builds server root trust pool using ServerCAPEM. Errors: ErrEmptyCA; wrapped ErrInvalidCACert on PEM append failures.
func LoadDeviceCAPool() (*x509.CertPool, error). Purpose: builds client device root trust pool using DeviceCAPEM. Errors: ErrEmptyCA; wrapped ErrInvalidCACert on PEM append failures.

Security Constraints: AppendCertsFromPEM enforces cryptographic format and structure verification. Empty inputs fail immediately to protect callers.
